Economy Minister Juan Sourrouillewas heading for Washington for talks with creditor banks onrescheduling part of Argentina's foreign debt.    Economy Ministry sources said he hoped to seal an agreementrescheduling 30 bln dlrs of private foreign debt.    Argentina, seeking 2.15 bln dlrs in fresh loans fromprivate international banks to meet 1987 growth targets, hasbeen negotiating with the banks' steering committee sinceFebruary.    Sourroille will also attend International Monetary Fund andWorld Bank meetings. REUTER&#3;